			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Junior System Administrator - New York</strong></p>
<p>
Livestream is an innovative and fast growing live video start-up based in New York which delivers over a billion minutes of video per month. We&#39;ve just launched the new version of our platform (http://new.livestream.com), and are looking for talented engineers to help us build and scale the most amazing live streaming service.</p>
<p>
We are looking for candidates who are passionate about building the tools that power major infrastructures, take pride in what they build, are quick learners and love to work in a challenging and fast-paced environment. As part of a start-up competing in a world-scale market, you will be expected to work hard and will have the ability to manage services used by millions of people.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate will have experience in system administration, with a focus on web operations and using monitoring, automation, and management tools.&nbsp; They will be part of a team of System Administrators that help to build and maintain the Livestream infrastructure, and will understand and believe the philosophy that anything that is worth doing multiple times is worth automating away.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work weekly day shifts including some weekend rotations.</li>
<li>
Install, configure, troubleshoot, monitor and measure&nbsp;our applications and our infrastructure.</li>
<li>
Maintain 100% uptime of our production services.</li>
<li>
Help to continuously improve our processes and tools to ensure the best possible experience for our users, from uptime to performance and reliability.</li>
<li>
Ensure that our monitoring tools catch and alert on all production issues without generating a flood of false positives.</li>
<li>
Follow escalation process through issue resolution, including providing documentation as to the solution and suggesting improvements to avoid future issues.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Follow regular operational procedures and complete all assigned tasks during the shift.</li>
<li>
Send periodic NOC reports with the current system and service status.</li>
<li>
Monitor backups and disaster recovery, including backup verification and performing restoration tests and participating in disaster recovery drills.</li>
<li>
Build our knowledge base by creating and updating documentation.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Build and maintain automation systems to reduce time for builds and deployments and to enable the team to scale its output exponentially over time.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<u>Experience using linux, preferably on physical, virtual, and cloud servers.</u></li>
<li>
Bachelors degree in Computer Science or&nbsp;IT, or equivalent work experience.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Strong written and verbal communication skills; ability to organize and prioritize tasks.</li>
<li>
Basic understanding of data center management, core networking, and serving static and streaming content over the web.</li>
<li>
Experience with unix scripting: shell, perl, python, ruby, or equivalent languages.</li>
<li>
Conceptual knowledge of DNS, DHCP, PXE installation, server virtualization technologies (XEN or equivalent) and database management.</li>
<li>
Experience using monitoring systems (Nagios, Zenoss, Cacti, or equivalents).</li>
<li>
Ability to work in fast-paced environments with weekly release schedules.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desired skills and experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience supporting a real-time, 24x7 production web environment.</li>
<li>
Experience using configuration management systems (chef, puppet, cfengine, etc.)</li>
<li>
Experience with package management (preferably on Debian systems).</li>
<li>
Experience managing MySQL or NoSQL databases.</li>
<li>
Experience using and managing webservers.</li>
<li>
Experience managing the following technologies or equivalents: ldap, ntp, dns, fai, dhcp, git, puppet, mysql, redis.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Start Date: Immediate</p>
